Write a URL using a given text-string and a given URL.
You can use the following code snippet to achieve this:

```javascript
function writeUrl(text, url) {
    return text + '://' + url;
}

// Example usage:
const text = 'https://www.example.com';
const url = 'https://www.google.com';
const writtenUrl = writeUrl(text, url);
console.log(writtenUrl); // Output: https://www.example.com://www.google.com
```

In this code snippet, the `writeUrl` function takes two parameters: `text` and `url`. It concatenates the `text` parameter with the `url` parameter using the `+` operator, and then appends a `://` separator to the end of the string

